{"type":"message","id":"4af82241","parentId":"40f5b0ed","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:55:48.829Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the images exist in the inbound media directory. I need to:\n\n1. First verify the cookies are valid by launching a quick headless test\n2. Then create a bug with:\n   - Title: \"玩家反馈咒语突破对月圆之夜无效\"\n   - Handler: 西奥 (this isn't in my known user list, but I can try the autocomplete approach)\n   - CC: 周以天 (兵王 - default for all bugs)\n   - Attachments: the 2 images\n\nFor attachments in TAPD, the bug create page likely has a file upload field. Let me check the bug-fields.md... it doesn't mention attachments specifically. In TAPD, attachments are typically uploaded via a file input or an attachment widget. I'll need to handle that.\n\nAlso, \"西奥\" is not in the known user list. Based on the context (this sounds like a game balance/design bug about cards), it might be a 策划 or a QA person. Let me just use the name and let the autocomplete figure it out.\n\nActually wait - I should first test the cookies. Let me write a quick check script.\n\nActually, let me just build a comprehensive script that:\n1. Launches Playwright\n2. Loads cookies\n3. Opens the bug create page\n4. Fills in all fields\n5. Uploads attachments (images)\n6. Submits\n\nBut first, I should check if the cookies are still valid. Let me write a quick validation script.\n\nLet me think about the TAPD attachment flow. In TAPD's bug create page, there's usually a file upload section where you can attach files. The upload is typically handled by an AJAX uploader. Let me look for the file input selector.\n\nCommon approaches in TAPD:\n- There's usually a `.uploadify-queue` or similar upload widget\n- File input might be `input[type=file]` with some custom styling\n- Or it could be a button that opens a file dialog\n\nLet me write a comprehensive script. First let me test cookies.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"先验证 Cookie 有效性，同时准备脚本。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FQ1djSxG7Bb9ieCZjuk03412","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace & node -e \"\nconst { chromium } = require('playwright');\nconst fs = require('fs');\n(async () => {\n  const cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled'] });\n  const ctx = await browser.newContext({ locale: 'zh-CN', userAgent: 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/125.0.0.0 Safari/537.36' });\n  await ctx.addCookies(cookies);\n  const page = await ctx.newPage();\n  await page.addInitScript(() => { delete navigator.webdriver; Object.defineProperty(navigator,'webdriver',{get:()=>false}); });\n  await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/bugtrace/bugs/add', { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 }).catch(e=>{});\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  const title = await page.title();\n  console.log('Page title:', title);\n  const url = page.url();\n  console.log('URL:', url);\n  const hasLogin = await page.evaluate(() => document.querySelector('#BugTitle') !== null);\n  console.log('BugTitle visible:', hasLogin);\n  console.log('Cookie valid:', hasLogin ? 'YES' : 'NO');\n  await browser.close();\n})();\n\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1936,"output":875,"cacheRead":33280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36091,"cost":{"input":0.00027104,"output":0.000245,"cacheRead":0.00093184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00144788}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778900141306,"responseId":"184a4108-13ce-4eda-8c7e-7793cc4e294c"}}
