{"type":"message","id":"853cf022","parentId":"1c591bb1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:35:23.016Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! TAPD autocomplete returns:\n- \"陈霄豪\" => suggestion: `豪)陈霄豪(陈霄豪)` — the display format is `豪)陈霄豪(陈霄豪)` or something similar\n- \"西奥\" => (none) — not found\n\nSo the correct name to use in TAPD is **陈霄豪**. The autocomplete works when I type \"陈霄豪\". The suggestion format appears to be something like `豪)陈霄豪(陈霄豪)` - when I type the name and select the suggestion, it will properly fill the hidden field.\n\nNow let me also check the rest of the page structure to understand attachments and submit button. Let me update the script to also inspect the page structure and then build the final create script.\n\nLet me write a more comprehensive inspection script that also looks at the attachment upload mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了，TAPD 上西奥的注册名是 **陈霄豪** ✅ \n\n现在解决附件上传方式，让我看看 TAPD 上传区域的 HTML。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZqDGUCH0GP64uWFBFHqT8323","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\inspect_upload.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.resolve('tapd_cookies.json');\n\n(async () => {\n  const cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, 'utf8'));\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled'] });\n  const ctx = await browser.newContext({ locale: 'zh-CN', viewport:{width:1920,height:1080}, userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0 Safari/537.36' });\n  await ctx.addCookies(cookies);\n  const page = await ctx.newPage();\n  await page.addInitScript(() => { delete navigator.webdriver; });\n  \n  await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/bugtrace/bugs/add', { waitUntil:'domcontentloaded', timeout:30000 }).catch(e=>{});\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\n  // Dump attachment section HTML\n  const html = await page.evaluate(() => {\n    // Find all file-related elements\n    const files = document.querySelectorAll('[id*=\"file\" i], [id*=\"attach\" i], [class*=\"file\" i], [class*=\"attach\" i], [class*=\"upload\" i]');\n    const results = [];\n    files.forEach(el => {\n      if (el.offsetParent !== null) {\n        results.push({\n          tag: el.tagName,\n          id: el.id,\n          class: el.className?.substring(0,150),\n          type: el.type || '',\n          text: el.textContent?.trim().substring(0,100),\n          html: el.outerHTML?.substring(0,300)\n        });\n      }\n    });\n    return results;\n  });\n  console.log('=== Visible attachment elements ===');\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(html, null, 2));\n\n  // Also check the submit buttons visible state\n  const submitInfo = await page.evaluate(() => {\n    return {\n      save_return: document.querySelector('#save_return')?.outerHTML?.substring(0,200),\n      _view: document.querySelector('#_view')?.outerHTML?.substring(0,200),\n      save_view: document.querySelector('#save_view')?.outerHTML?.substring(0,200),\n    };\n  });\n  console.log('\\n=== Submit buttons ===');\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(submitInfo, null, 2));\n\n  // Try to find file input\n  const fileInputs = await page.evaluate(() => {\n    return Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input[type=\"file\"]')).map(i => ({\n      id: i.id,\n      class: i.className,\n      html: i.outerHTML?.substring(0,200),\n      parentHtml: i.parentElement?.outerHTML?.substring(0,200)\n    }));\n  });\n  console.log('\\n=== File inputs ===');\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(fileInputs, null, 2));\n\n  await browser.close();\n})();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":85,"output":978,"cacheRead":44160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45223,"cost":{"input":0.000011900000000000001,"output":0.00027384,"cacheRead":