{"type":"message","id":"79551397","parentId":"3e23c6e9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:35:55.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, rather than running the full script which will open a headed browser and take a long time, let me think more carefully about the attachment approach.\n\nLooking at the HTML structure again:\n1. Visible attachment button: `<a id=\"upload-attachement\" class=\"link-ico f12 dropdown-toggle\" href=\"javascript:;\">...<b>添加</b></a>`\n2. The dropdown has a `<a class=\"multi-local-upload\" title=\"本地上传\">` which contains `#file_input`\n3. Hidden form: `<form id=\"attachmentsForm\" class=\"hidden\" ...>` with `#file_input` inside\n\nSo the flow is:\n- Click `#upload-attachement` → dropdown shows\n- In the dropdown, click `<a class=\"multi-local-upload\">` → system file dialog opens\n- User selects file → AJAX upload happens\n\nFor Playwright automation:\n- The simplest approach is to directly interact with the `#file_input` element\n- The first `#file_input` (inside `<a class=\"multi-local-upload\">`) might be invisible but Playwright's `setInputFiles` works on hidden inputs\n- Or I can use the second one in `#attachmentsForm`\n\nActually, `setInputFiles` works on `<input type=\"file\">` elements regardless of visibility. Let me try.\n\nBut to trigger the upload, I need the upload button to be clicked first (to open the dropdown), then the file input should be set. Or maybe I can just set the file directly without clicking anything.\n\nActually, Playwright's `setInputFiles` should work by directly setting the value of the file input, which should trigger the `change` event. Let me check if this triggers the upload or if the \"添加\" button needs to be clicked first.\n\nIn most modern file upload implementations, calling `setInputFiles` directly should work because:\n1. It sets the file on the input\n2. This triggers a `change` event\n3. The JavaScript listener picks up the change and starts the upload\n\nLet me just run the script and see what happens.\n\nActually, the issue is the script uses headless: false, which means it'll open a browser. This is intentional because TAPD might WAF-block headless mode. Let me try with headless: true first this time since we've confirmed the cookie works.\n\nWait, actually looking at the previous successful bug creation approach (create_bug.mjs), it uses headless: false as default. The original script had `headless = false` for reliability.\n\nLet me just run it and see what happens. But wait - the browser will open up in headed mode which means it will pop up on the user's screen. That could be annoying. Let me make it headless first to test, and only fall back to headed if WAF blocks.\n\nLet me modify the script to be headless first.\n\nActually, I'll just run it as is but change to headless: true. Let me recreate the file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YJbFai1zEKXf3CGNp9ux0935","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\create_bug_v3.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"    headless: false,","newText":"    headless: true,"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":110,"output":732,"cacheRead":49664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50506,"cost":{"input":0.0000154,"output":0.00020496000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001390592,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001610952}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778902547751,"responseId":"c878176f-3e33-4860-9650-e2a913f8c077"}}
