{"type":"message","id":"1e88f046","parentId":"0965d8b3","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:42:20.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, this approach seems overly complicated and time-consuming. Let me try a more direct approach - open the bug edit page, which should have a delete button more prominently displayed, or use the list view where you can select and delete.\n\nActually, thinking about this more practically - TAPD's bug list view has checkboxes and a batch delete option. Let me try that approach instead.\n\nOr wait, even simpler - let me just try to find the API endpoint for deleting bugs. From the earlier research, I found:\n- POST /api/aggregation/bug_aggregation/get_bugs_list\n- POST /api/aggregation/workitem_aggregation/common_get_info\n\nThere must be a delete endpoint. Let me check the page's JavaScript for API call patterns.\n\nActually, you know what, let me just try to use the edit page URL: `https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/bugtrace/bugs/edit?id=1131253609001016524`\n\nOn the edit page, there might be more visible delete options.\n\nBut actually, let me just run this script and see what happens. It should work.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_pz2ADH5qdh8Y4pi4dZFA9041","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Set-Location C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node delete_v3.mjs 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":149,"output":321,"cacheRead":66816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67286,"cost":{"input":0.00002086,"output":0.00008988,"cacheRead":0.001870848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001981588}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778902936585,"responseId":"23a3b097-8301-45cd-ae73-c3595a2ba4d3"}}
