tories/add` might mean the submission didn't redirect properly, or it redirected to the same page after creating. The \"execution context was destroyed\" error suggests a navigation happened.\n\nActually, the most likely scenario: the form was submitted successfully, and the page navigated to either a detail page or back to the same page. By the time the code runs `page.url()`, the page might have already navigated.\n\nLet me try with a simpler approach - just wait for a specific URL or look at the final URL.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"提交成功了但页面导航导致上下文销毁。让我看看最终结果。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tB3tPV137w3QACxDKdyj0184","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\create_story.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"    // Submit via #btn_save_view\n    await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n    await page.click('#btn_save_view');\n    await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\n    const resultUrl = page.url();\n    console.log('\\nResult URL:', resultUrl);\n\n    if (!resultUrl.includes('stories/add')) {\n      console.log('\\n🎉 Story created!');\n      console.log('URL:', resultUrl);\n    } else {\n      const errors = await page.evaluate(() => {\n        return Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.error,[class*=error]'))\n          .map(e => e.textContent?.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n      });\n      console.log('⚠️ Errors:', errors.join(', ') || 'form validation error');\n    }","newText":"    // Submit via #btn_save_view\n    await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n\n    // Wait for navigation or stay\n    await Promise.all([\n      page.waitForURL('**/*', { timeout: 10000 }).catch(() => {}),\n      page.click('#btn_save_view'),\n    ]);\n    await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n\n    const resultUrl = page.url();\n    console.log('\\nFinal URL:', resultUrl);\n\n    if (!resultUrl.includes('stories/add') || resultUrl.includes('story/detail')) {\n      console.log('\\n🎉 Story created!');\n      console.log('URL:', resultUrl