{"type":"message","id":"1ac3153f","parentId":"91a2e5b2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:12:08.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I'm using `$()` for jQuery but on the Story page, I don't know if jQuery is available. Let me try with native DOM events instead, or just use Playwright's click method.\n\nActually, looking at the page structure earlier, the edit icon was:\n```html\n<span class=\"edit-workitems-relation j-edit-preset-stories\">\n  <i class=\"font font-edit\"></i>\n</span>\n```\n\nClicking this `.j-edit-preset-stories` should open the dialog. But in my earlier inspect_dialog.mjs test, when I clicked it, the dialog remained hidden (`style=\"display: none\"`). This could be because:\n1. The click didn't trigger the Vue event properly in headless mode\n2. Or the event handler needs a specific approach\n\nLet me try clicking with Playwright's native click and using `force: true`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_5NM5oCDdrxO6ecy5RaDQ7958","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\inspect_preset_dialog.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"// Open the dialog by clicking the edit icon\nawait page.evaluate(() => {\n  $('.j-edit-preset-stories').trigger('click');\n});\nawait page.waitForTimeout(3000);","newText":"// Try clicking the edit icon via Playwright\nawait page.locator('.j-edit-preset-stories').click({force: true});\nawait page.waitForTimeout(3000);"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":151,"output":366,"cacheRead":121856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122373,"cost":{"input":0.00002114,"output":0.00010248000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003411968,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003535588}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778911923534,"responseId":"60d26155-a244-45c0-a9d0-9c7f6585b58b"}}
