{"type":"message","id":"9fb2e6a6","parentId":"e2f16801","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:12:32.813Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ET_6hSgCyxP2pwy5ybAwcCM5824","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<div class=\"el-dialog__wrapper\" width=\"962px\" style=\"display: none;\"><div role=\"dialog\" aria-modal=\"true\" aria-label=\"dialog\" class=\"el-dialog agi-dialog agi-dialog--small agi-dialog--no-footer video-dialog\" style=\"margin-top: 15vh; width: 962px;\"><div class=\"el-dialog__header\"><div class=\"agi-dialog__header agi-dialog__header--no-title\"><i class=\"agi-icon tapd-icon-close-v2 agi-dialog__close-icon\"></i></div><!----></div><!----><!----></div></div>\n\nProcess exited with signal SIGKILL."}],"details":{"status":"failed","sessionId":"fast-claw","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"<div class=\"el-dialog__wrapper\" width=\"962px\" style=\"display: none;\"><div role=\"dialog\" aria-modal=\"true\" aria-label=\"dialog\" class=\"el-dialog agi-dialog agi-dialog--small agi-dialog--no-footer video-dialog\" style=\"margin-top: 15vh; width: 962px;\"><div class=\"el-dialog__header\"><div class=\"agi-dialog__header agi-dialog__header--no-title\"><i class=\"agi-icon tapd-icon-close-v2 agi-dialog__close-icon\"></i></div><!----></div><!----><!----></div></div>\n","name":"Set-Location C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace;"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778911952813}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e237b5e","parentId":"9fb2e6a6","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:12:44.764Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The dialog is still `display: none`. The click via Playwright didn't trigger the dialog to show. This is likely because the dialog is a Vue 2 component that needs a specific event to be triggered.\n\nLooking at the dialog structure - it uses `el-dialog` from Element UI (Vue). The `style=\"display: none\"` is the default state. The dialog shows when a Vue data property changes.\n\nThe `.j-edit-preset-stories` click handler is likely a Vue event listener. Maybe I need to trigger it differently.\n\nLet me look at the HTML more carefully. The structure around the edit button was:\n```html\n<span class=\"edit-workitems-relation j-edit-preset-stories\">\n  <i class=\"font font-edit\"></i>\n</span>\n```\n\nAnd the dialog has a Vue component placeholder:\n```html\n<div class=\"fe-vue-component\"><!----></div>\n```\n\nThe dialog is rendered by a Vue component that's connected via `vueComponentConnect`. The click on `.j-edit-preset-stories` probably dispatches an event to this Vue component.\n\nLet me try a different approach - instead of clicking the UI element, let me directly manipulate the Vue component's data or dispatch the proper event.\n\nActually, looking at the earlier HTML output more carefully:\n```html\n<script id=\"preset-dialog-story__template\" type=\"text/html\">\n<script id=\"preset-dialog-task__template\" type=\"text/html\">\n```\n\nThese are Underscore.js templates. The dialog uses a custom TAPD dialog system, not pure Vue. Let me look for a JavaScript function that opens the dialog.\n\nIn TAPD's older UI, they often use a global function like `tapd.openDialog()` or similar. Let me try a different approach - look for what event listener is attached to `.j-edit-preset-stories`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KThX8EDcGfiMaXctBnds9371","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\find_dialog_trigger.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({headless:true,args:['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled']});\nconst ctx = await browser.newContext({locale:'zh-CN',viewport:{width:1920,height:1080},userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0'});\nawait ctx.addCookies(cookies);\nconst page = await ctx.newPage();\nawait page.addInitScript(()=>{delete navigator.webdriver;Object.defineProperty(navigator,'webdriver',{get:()=>false})});\nawait page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/prong/stories/add',{waitUntil:'domcontentloaded',timeout:30000}).catch(e=>{});\nawait page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\nconst info = await page.evaluate(() => {\n  // Check what's bound to the click event\n  const el = document.querySelector('.j-edit-preset-stories');\n  if (!el) return 'Element not found';\n  \n  // Try to find its click handler\n  const events = [];\n  \n  // Check Vue-specific bindings\n  if (el.__vue__) {\n    events.push('Has Vue binding');\n    events.push('Vue events: ' + Object.keys(el.__vue__._events || {}).join(', '));\n  }\n  \n  // Try jQuery data (old approach)\n  if (typeof $ !== 'undefined') {\n    const $events = $._data(el, 'events');\n    if ($events) events.push('jQuery events: ' + Object.keys($events).join(', '));\n  }\n  \n  // Check onclick attribute\n  events.push('onclick: ' + (el.getAttribute('onclick') || 'none'));\n  \n  // Look at parent/child listeners  \n  const child = el.querySelector('i.font-edit');\n  if (child) {\n    if (child.onclick) events.push('Child onclick: ' + child.onclick.toString().substring(0,200));\n    events.push('Child __vue__: ' + (child.__vue__ ? 'yes' : 'no'));\n  }\n  \n  return events;\n});\n\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(info, null, 2));\n\n// Also check for the Vue component that renders the dialog\nconst vueComp = await page.evaluate(() => {\n  const comp = document.querySelector('.fe-vue-component');\n  if (!comp) return 'No fe-vue-component';\n  return {\n    html: comp.outerHTML?.substring(0,500),\n    siblings: comp.parentElement?.innerHTML?.substring(0,500)\n  };\n});\nconsole.log('\\nVue component:', JSON.stringify(vueComp, null, 2));\n\nawait browser.close();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":182,"output":1097,"cacheRead":122624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123903,"cost":{"input":0.000025480000000000003,"output":0.00030716,"cacheRead":0.003433472,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003766112}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778911952816,"responseId":"90d638d9-d90b-40a7-86f8-af74ca927e6e"}}
