{"type":"message","id":"ff5a9441","parentId":"3f53445e","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:13:33.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still not working. The jQuery trigger also didn't open the dialog. This is strange.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Maybe the TAPD Story creation page uses a different mechanism. The dialog is rendered as a Vue component (`fe-vue-component`) inside the same container. The `.j-edit-preset-stories` click handler probably calls a Vue method, not a regular jQuery event.\n\nLooking at the HTML:\n```html\n<div class=\"associated-object-item preset-sub-object\" style=\"\">\n  <span class=\"workitem-relations-title\">预设子工作项</span>\n  <span class=\"edit-workitems-relation j-edit-preset-stories\">\n     <i class=\"font font-edit\"></i>\n  </span>\n  <input type=\"hidden\" class=\"j-auto-succeed-name__form\" name=\"data[auto_succeed_story_name]\" value=\"1\">\n  <input type=\"hidden\" class=\"j-auto-succeed-fields__form\" name=\"data[auto_succeed_story_fields]\">\n  <div class=\"preset-story-names-icon\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"fe-vue-component\">\n  <!-- The Vue dialog is rendered here -->\n</div>\n```\n\nThe `fe-vue-component` is a placeholder that the Vue component renders into. The click handler on `.j-edit-preset-stories` probably communicates with the Vue component to show the dialog.\n\nMaybe I need to look at the attached JavaScript to understand the connection mechanism. There's a script referenced: `vueComponentConnect-1c8964cba2.js`. This script is responsible for connecting the regular DOM events to the Vue component.\n\nThe `vueComponentConnect` library probably listens for click events on certain selectors and triggers Vue component methods accordingly. The selector might be `.j-edit-preset-stories`.\n\nBut the event isn't being triggered by Playwright's click or dispatchEvent. Maybe the event listener uses event delegation on a parent element, not directly on the `.j-edit-preset-stories`.\n\nLet me try a different approach - instead of trying to open the dialog, let me try to directly modify the form data that gets submitted. The preset items might be submitted as part of the form data, not read from the dialog.\n\nLooking at the hidden inputs found earlier:\n- `data[PresetItems][12][create_task]` with value \"false\"\n- etc.\n\nThese are hidden inputs on the page. When I changed their values via evaluate, they should have been submitted with the form. But the user said it still created all 17.\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that the `create_task` values in the hidden inputs ARE correct (false for all except 3), but the TAPD backend ignores them because the dialog wasn't used to confirm the selection. Or perhaps the form submit sends the data differently.\n\nLet me look at this from a completely different angle. Instead of trying to disable presets through the UI, maybe I should:\n\n1. Check the actual form data submitted to understand the format\n2. Or try to intercept the form submission\n3. Or use a different approach altogether\n\nActually, wait. Let me check something - after Page submission, maybe the presets DID get limited to 12,14,16, but the TAPD page showed \"17\" as a default text. The user might have seen \"将同步创建 17 项\" text and assumed all 17 were created. Let me verify by checking the actual created story.\n\nActually, the user said \"开的单子还是全都有\" - meaning they checked the actual created story and saw all 17 items. So my approach of modifying hidden inputs didn't work.\n\nLet me try yet another approach. Maybe I need to directly interact with the Vue component to set the data. Or maybe I need to use a completely different method to submit the form with specific preset items.\n\nLet me look at how the form is submitted. The submit button `#btn_save_view` triggers the form submission. Before submitting, the form serializes all inputs. The preset hidden inputs should be included.\n\nBut wait - maybe there's JavaScript validation before submission that reads the `j-auto-succeed-fields__form` hidden field and uses that to determine which presets to create, overriding the individual `create_task` fields.\n\nLet me check what `data[auto_succeed_story_fields]` contains.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Cs7Rzle7zNx3gnlfSSBP9851","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\check_submit.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({headless:true,args:['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled']});\nconst ctx = await browser.newContext({locale:'zh-CN',viewport:{width:1920,height:1080},userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0'});\nawait ctx.addCookies(cookies);\nconst page = await ctx.newPage();\nawait page.addInitScript(()=>{delete navigator.webdriver;Object.defineProperty(navigator,'webdriver',{get:()=>false})});\n\n// Intercept network requests\nconst requests = [];\npage.on('request', req => {\n  if (req.url().includes('tapd.cn') && req.method() === 'POST') {\n    const body = req.postData()?.substring(0,2000) || '';\n    if (body.includes('create_task') || body.includes('PresetItems') || body.includes('save_return') || body.includes('stories/save')) {\n      requests.push({url: req.url().substring(0,150), body: body});\n    }\n  }\n});\n\nawait page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/prong/stories/add',{waitUntil:'domcontentloaded',timeout:30000}).catch(e=>{});\nawait page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\n// Fill in required fields  \nawait page.fill('#StoryName', 'test-preset-check');\nawait page.selectOption('#StoryPriority', 'P2');\nawait page.selectOption('#StoryVersion', '【1V1】正式版本V2.0');\n\n// Set preset items (only enable 12,14,16)\nawait page.evaluate(() => {\n  const tasks = document.querySelectorAll('input[name*=\"PresetItems\"][name*=\"[create_task]\"]');\n  tasks.forEach(input => {\n    const match = input.name.match(/\\[(\\d+)\\]/);\n    if (match) {\n      const idx = parseInt(match[1]);\n      input.value = [12, 14, 16].includes(idx) ? 'true' : 'false';\n      input.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));\n    }\n  });\n});\n\n// Also check auto_succeed_story_fields\nconst hiddenFields = await page.evaluate(() => {\n  const fields = document.querySelector('input[name=\"data[auto_succeed_story_fields]\"]');\n  return fields?.value || 'no field';\n});\nconsole.log('auto_succeed_story_fields:', hiddenFields);\n\n// Submit and capture the POST data\nawait page.click('#btn_save_view');\nawait page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\n// Print captured requests\nconsole.log('\\nCaptured POST requests:');\nrequests.forEach((r, i) => {\n  console.log(`\\n--- Request #${i} ---`);\n  console.log('URL:', r.url);\n  console.log('Body:', r.body);\n});\n\nawait browser.close();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":119,"output":1655,"cacheRead":125440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127214,"cost":{"input":0.00001666,"output":0.00046340000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0035123199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00399238}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778911997610,"responseId":"c4088791-593b-49db-8a46-7cfb31f9774e"}}
