{"type":"message","id":"c79c9b01","parentId":"848732d4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:14:00.045Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No POST requests were captured, meaning the page navigated before any POST was intercepted, or the form submission used a different mechanism (like an AJAX call that went through before the listener was set up).\n\nWait, the page.on('request') should work for all requests. Maybe the form submit didn't include create_task parameters because an AJAX call or something else handled the save.\n\nActually, looking at the result - no POST requests at all were captured from tapd.cn paths that include create_task. This might mean the form submission uses a standard form POST (which causes navigation), and Playwright's page.on('request') only captures XHR/fetch requests, not form navigations.\n\nAlso, the auto_succeed_story_fields was empty (\"no field\"), which means the hidden input existed but had no value.\n\nLet me try a different approach - instead of intercepting, let me try to actually trigger the dialog. Let me look at what JavaScript file handles the click on `.j-edit-preset-stories`.\n\nActually, I think the key is `vueComponentConnect`. This library connects static HTML elements to Vue components. The `.j-edit-preset-stories` probably triggers a Vue component method via `vueComponentConnect`. Let me look for how to call it.\n\nActually, let me try yet another approach. Instead of trying to open the dialog, let me directly modify the form data right before submission by overriding the form's submit handler.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"让我尝试另一种方式——在表单提交前直接拦截并修改 preset 数据。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_zgwA3BvZ0G48pDijsX4P3879","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\test_preset_override.mjs","content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({headless:true,args:['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled']});\nconst ctx = await browser.newContext({locale:'zh-CN',viewport:{width:1920,height:1080},userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0'});\nawait ctx.addCookies(cookies);\nconst page = await ctx.newPage();\nawait page.addInitScript(()=>{delete navigator.webdriver;Object.defineProperty(navigator,'webdriver',{get:()=>false})});\n\n// Intercept form action\nlet intercepted = false;\npage.on('request', req => {\n  if (req.method() === 'POST' && req.url().includes('/stories/save')) {\n    const data = req.postData() || '';\n    console.log('=== POST data intercepted ===');\n    console.log(data);\n    intercepted = true;\n  }\n});\n\nawait page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/prong/stories/add',{waitUntil:'domcontentloaded',timeout:30000}).catch(e=>{});\nawait page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\n// Fill form\nawait page.fill('#StoryName', 'test-preset-2');\nawait page.selectOption('#StoryPriority', 'P2');\nawait page.selectOption('#StoryVersion', '【1V1】正式版本V2.0');\n\n// Override form submit handler to inject preset data  \nawait page.evaluate(() => {\n  // Before form submit, set correct preset values\n  const form = document.querySelector('form');\n  if (!form) return;\n  \n  form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {\n    const tasks = document.querySelectorAll('input[name*=\"PresetItems\"][name*=\"[create_task]\"]');\n    tasks.forEach(input => {\n      const match = input.name.match(/\\[(\\d+)\\]/);\n      if (match) {\n        const idx = parseInt(match[1]);\n        // Only keep 12(客户端), 14(策划), 16(QA)\n        input.value = [12, 14, 16].includes(idx) ? 'true' : 'false';\n      }\n    });\n    console.log('Submit handler fired, presets modified');\n  }, true); // useCapture to fire before other handlers\n});\n\n// Submit\nawait page.click('#btn_save_view');\nawait page.waitForTimeout(8000);\n\nif (!intercepted) {\n  console.log('\\nNo POST intercepted - checking page state...');\n  console.log('Current URL:', page.url());\n  // Check if page navigated\n  try {\n    const errors = await page.evaluate(() => {\n      return Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.error,[class*=error]')).map(e=>e.textContent?.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n    });\n    console.log('Errors:', errors.join(', ') || 'none');\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.log('Page ctx destroyed (navigation)');\n  }\n}\n\nawait browser.close();\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":79,"output":1066,"cacheRead":127488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128633,"cost":{"input":0.00001106,"output":0.00029848,"cacheRead":0.0035696639999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003879204}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778912029361,"responseId":"bab6ec87-e2aa-4e0c-a7cd-37ec1e976fba"}}
