{"type":"message","id":"1b7828e0","parentId":"c5a4ea8d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:14:45.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, this approach is taking too long and is getting too complex. Let me take a fundamentally different approach.\n\nInstead of trying to figure out the Vue dialog, let me:\n1. Create the story with the default 17 presets\n2. Then use the story edit page or child tasks API to delete the unwanted ones\n\nOR, maybe let me try to find the POST URL for saving presets. Looking at the TAPD network patterns:\n- The form action for stories is probably `/31253609/prong/stories/save`\n- Maybe there's an API endpoint for presets\n\nActually wait - let me re-check something. In the page HTML earlier, the `fe-vue-component` renders the Vue dialog. The dialog shows/hides based on a Vue property. But `vueComponentConnect` might handle the communication between the DOM click and Vue.\n\nLet me look at what `vueComponentConnect` does in the page by examining the script.\n\nActually, the quickest way to figure this out is to just open the page in headed mode and manually inspect it. But since I can't see the screen, let me try another approach entirely.\n\nWhat if the issue isn't about setting the create_task values at all? What if the `create_task` hidden inputs I'm modifying aren't the right ones? Let me look more carefully at the form structure.\n\nActually wait - I just realized something. The form submit goes through and the story IS created (I got \"navigation detected\"). But the presets that are created are all 17. This means the form submission defers to the template settings, not the hidden input values.\n\nIn TAPD, when creating a story, the preset items are auto-generated from the template's definition. The `data[PresetItems][N][create_task]` inputs are probably only read when the dialog is opened and saved. If the dialog was never opened, the backend uses the template defaults.\n\nSo the key is: **open the dialog → check/uncheck the presets → save dialog → then submit the form**.\n\nLet me think about how to force-open this dialog. Looking at the page HTML:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"fe-vue-component\">\n  <!-- Vue renders the dialog here -->\n  <div class=\"el-dialog__wrapper\" width=\"962px\" style=\"display: none;\">\n    ...\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nThe dialog is a Vue component. The `j-edit-preset-stories` click sends a message to the Vue component via `vueComponentConnect`. The Vue component then sets `dialogVisible = true` which changes the dialog's display.\n\nThe `vueComponentConnect` library likely uses a global event bus or a data attribute to communicate. Let me look for the connect mechanism.\n\nActually, I noticed earlier that the `fe-vue-component` div contains:\n```html\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/js_dist/vueComponentConnect-1c8964cba2.js\"></script>\n```\n\nThis script connects the DOM element `.j-edit-preset-stories` to the Vue component. The connection is probably done through a data attribute like `data-vue-component` or through a JavaScript API.\n\nLet me try another approach - let me look at what data attributes or global functions are available.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Nk2HoB8wuK9cq0IStKWI5605","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Set-Location C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst c = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\nconst b = await chromium.launch({headless:true,args:['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled']});\nconst ctx = await b.newContext({locale:'zh-CN',viewport:{width:1920,height:1080},userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0'});\nawait ctx.addCookies(c);\nconst p = await ctx.newPage();\nawait p.addInitScript(()=>{delete navigator.webdriver;});\nawait p.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/prong/stories/add',{waitUntil:'domcontentloaded',timeout:30000}).catch(e=>{});\nawait p.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\nconst info = await p.evaluate(() => {\n  const results = {};\n  // Check for any fn that references preset\n  let keys = Object.keys(window).filter(k => k.toLowerCase().includes('preset') || k.toLowerCase().includes('dialog'));\n  results.windowKeys = keys;\n  \n  // Check data attributes on j-edit-preset-stories\n  const el = document.querySelector('.j-edit-preset-stories');\n  if (el) {\n    const data = {};\n    for (let attr of el.attributes) data[attr.name] = attr.value;\n    results.elementData = data;\n  }\n  \n  // Look for any global event bus or TAPD global\n  results.tapdGlobal = typeof window.TAPD !== 'undefined';\n  results.vueComponentConnect = typeof window.vueComponentConnect !== 'undefined';\n  \n  return results;\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(info,null,2));\nawait b.close();\n\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":72,"output":1156,"cacheRead":130176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131404,"cost":{"input":0.00001008,"output":0.00032368,"cacheRead":0.003644928,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003978688}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778912072592,"responseId":"8632bc1f-f475-40eb-b3b7-07d9d78b2c81"}}
