{"type":"message","id":"ca0183f6","parentId":"43ff9ef7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:15:26.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `PresetTaskDialog` is an object, not a function. The `presetWorkitemsHelper` has methods like `initworkitem` and `validateWorkitems`. And there's `presetWorkitemsTree` and `data`.\n\nLet me look at the structure more carefully. The helper has:\n- `presetWorkitemFields` - field names\n- `initworkitem` - initialization\n- `configs` - configurations\n- `container` - DOM container\n- `validateWorkitems` - validation\n- `presetWorkitemsTree` - tree structure\n- `data` - preset data\n\nLet me check `configs` and `data` and see if there's a way to:\n1. Show the dialog \n2. Modify the selections\n3. Confirm\n\nBut actually, this is getting way too deep into the implementation. Let me try a completely different and more practical approach:\n\n**Since the dialog is a Vue component, let me try to directly manipulate the Vue instance.**\n\nOr even better - let me try opening the dialog by calling the right method on the Vue component. Let me look at the Vue component attached to the `.fe-vue-component` element.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZPZfQqDkaQohgHtHbQUJ2692","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Set-Location C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst c = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('tapd_cookies.json','utf8'));\nconst b = await chromium.launch({headless:true,args:['--no-sandbox','--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled']});\nconst ctx = await b.newContext({locale:'zh-CN',viewport:{width:1920,height:1080},userAgent:'Mozilla/5.0...Chrome/125.0.0.0'});\nawait ctx.addCookies(c);\nconst p = await ctx.newPage();\nawait p.addInitScript(()=>{delete navigator.webdriver;});\nawait p.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/prong/stories/add',{waitUntil:'domcontentloaded',timeout:30000}).catch(e=>{});\nawait p.waitForTimeout(5000);\n\nconst info = await p.evaluate(() => {\n  const r = {};\n  // Check the configs object\n  if (presetWorkitemsHelper && presetWorkitemsHelper.configs) {\n    r.configs = String(presetWorkitemsHelper.configs).substring(0,500);\n  }\n  // Check data\n  if (presetWorkitemsHelper && presetWorkitemsHelper.data) {\n    r.data = typeof presetWorkitemsHelper.data;\n    if (typeof presetWorkitemsHelper.data === 'object' && presetWorkitemsHelper.data.length) {\n      r.dataLen = presetWorkitemsHelper.data.length;\n      r.dataFirst = JSON.stringify(presetWorkitemsHelper.data[0]).substring(0,200);\n    } else if (typeof presetWorkitemsHelper.data === 'object') {\n      r.dataKeys = Object.keys(presetWorkitemsHelper.data).slice(0,10);\n    }\n  }\n  // Check container\n  if (presetWorkitemsHelper.container) r.container = String(presetWorkitemsHelper.container).substring(0,200);\n  // Check if there's a showDialog or open function anywhere\n  const allKeys = {};\n  Object.getOwnPropertyNames(window).forEach(k => {\n    if (k.toLowerCase().includes('dialog') || k.toLowerCase().includes('preset') || k.toLowerCase().includes('workitem')) {\n      allKeys[k] = typeof window[k];\n    }\n  });\n  r.relatedGlobals = allKeys;\n  return r;\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(info,null,2));\nawait b.close();\n\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":257,"output":864,"cacheRead":133120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134241,"cost":{"input":0.000035980000000000004,"output":0.00024192000000000001,"cacheRead":0.00372736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00400526}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778912119263,"responseId":"c8c70165-a79e-4574-8f81-0c53b6e82816"}}
