{"type":"message","id":"88aa5e14","parentId":"b1cbf2db","timestamp":"2026-05-16T06:38:03.228Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the previous attempt removed all 17 presets. The issue is that the dialog removed all rows, including 客户端 (12), 策划 (14), and QA (16). \n\nThe problem might be that when I click the remove button (`.j-remove-row`) on a row, jQuery/Vue intercepts the click and removes the row from the DOM, but this changes the indices/order for subsequent operations. Or maybe the `parseInt` wasn't working correctly.\n\nActually, looking at it again - the original `tree-row` elements all have `idx` attributes from 0-16. When I query `document.querySelectorAll('.tree-row')`, I get them all. For each one, I check if the idx is in the keep list [12, 14, 16]. If not, I click `.j-remove-row`.\n\nBut wait - maybe clicking the remove button triggers an animation/hide, not an immediate DOM removal. So all the rows still exist when we check them, and ALL .j-remove-row buttons get clicked.\n\nOr maybe the issue is that after clicking remove on one row, the dialog re-renders/re-indexes, causing the idx attributes to change.\n\nLet me try a different approach:\n1. First, find the specific rows I want to REMOVE (not keep)\n2. Remove them one at a time, or use a more targeted selector\n\nActually, let me try a different approach entirely. Instead of removing rows I don't want, let me try to only keep the rows I want. Or even better - let me use a more targeted approach:\n\n1. After opening the dialog, find the rows by their name value (客户端, 策划, QA)\n2. Remove ALL other rows by iterating backwards (from the last row to the first)\n\nOr even simpler - let me directly manipulate the hidden inputs after the dialog is closed. Maybe the dialog just updates the hidden PresetItems inputs, and I can set them directly after the dialog submits.\n\nWait, let me think about this differently. The dialog shows 17 rows. When you click the X on a row, the row is removed from the dialog. When you click 提交, the dialog saves which rows remain. Then when you submit the main form, it creates sub-stories for the remaining presets.\n\nSo the issue might be that:\n1. I open the dialog\n2. I try to remove 14 rows (keeping 12, 14, 16)\n3. But clicking remove button causes jQuery to process each removal, and the DOM changes with each removal\n4. By the time I've processed all, all 17 rows might have been affected\n\nLet me look at the dialog HTML structure more carefully. Each tree-row has an idx attribute. If I iterate over all rows and click remove on the ones I don't want, the DOM might change between iterations, causing the idx values to shift.\n\nA better approach: collect all the rows I want to remove first, then remove them in reverse order (from the last to the first), so the indices don't shift.\n\nOr even better: find the rows by their name/input value rather than by index.\n\nLet me look at the HTML - each row has an input with class `workitem-template-name` and a value like \"原画草稿\", \"客户端\", etc. I can identify rows to keep by their input value.\n\nLet me rewrite the dialog optimization part.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，之前的问题可能是删除后 DOM 变化导致索引错乱了。这次按名称来精准操作。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UUqD5wMzkWui6CHa7f3Q3973","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\create_story.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"      // Configure preset items via dialog\n      // 1. Open the preset dialog\n      await page.evaluate(() => {\n        if (PresetTaskDialog && PresetTaskDialog.showDialog) PresetTaskDialog.showDialog();\n      });\n      await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n\n      // 2. Remove unwanted preset rows (keep only the ones in presetIndexes)\n      const removeCount = await page.evaluate((keepIndexes) => {\n        const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.tree-row');\n        let removed = 0;\n        rows.forEach(row => {\n          const idx = parseInt(row.getAttribute('idx') || '-1');\n          if (idx >= 0 && !keepIndexes.includes(idx)) {\n            const removeBtn = row.querySelector('.j-remove-row');\n            if (removeBtn) {\n              removeBtn.click();\n              removed++;\n            }\n          }\n        });\n        return removed;\n      }, presetIndexes);\n      console.log(`✅ Preset dialog: removed ${removeCount} items, kept indexes ${presetIndexes.join(', ')}`);\n\n      // 3. Save dialog - click submit\n      await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n      await page.evaluate(() => {\n        const saveBtn = document.querySelector('.j-modify-preset-stories');\n        if (saveBtn) saveBtn.click();\n      });\n      await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n\n      // 4. Wait for dialog to close\n      await page.waitForTimeout(2000);","newText":"      // Configure preset items via dialog\n      const KEEP_NAMES = ['客户端', '策划', 'QA'];\n\n      // 1. Open the preset dialog\n      await page.evaluate(() => {\n        if (PresetTaskDialog && PresetTaskDialog.showDialog) PresetTaskDialog.showDialog();\n      });\n      await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n\n      // 2. Remove unwanted rows by name - iterate backwards to avoid index shifting\n      await page.evaluate((keepNames) => {\n        let removed = 0;\n        // Collect rows to remove (by name input value)\n        const rowsToRemove = [];\n        const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.tree-row');\n        rows.forEach(row => {\n          const nameInput = row.querySelector('.workitem-template-name.j-row-cell--name');\n          if (nameInput && !keepNames.includes(nameInput.value)) {\n            rowsToRemove.push(row);\n          }\n        });\n        // Remove in reverse (last to first) to avoid index shifting\n        for (let i = rowsToRemove.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n          const removeBtn = rowsToRemove[i].querySelector('.j-remove-row');\n          if (removeBtn) {\n            removeBtn.click();\n            removed++;\n          }\n        }\n        return removed;\n      }, KEEP_NAMES);\n      console.log(`✅ Preset dialog: kept 客户端, 策划, QA only`);\n\n      // 3. Save dialog - click submit\n      await page.waitForTimeout(500);\n      await page.evaluate(() => {\n        const saveBtn = document.querySelector('.j-modify-preset-stories');\n        if (saveBtn) saveBtn.click();\n      });\n      await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n\n      // 4. Wait for dialog to close\n      await page.waitForTimeout(2000);"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":32073,"output":1622,"cacheRead":118400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152095,"cost":{"input":0.0044902200000000005,"output":0.00045416000000000006,"cacheRead":0.0033152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00825958}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778913464315,"responseId":"4a618d1b-6635-47d6-8d24-45215092df3a"}}
